WEBVTT

00:01.933 --> 00:03.933
[ Wind Whistling ]

00:05.000 --> 00:11.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:21.733 --> 00:24.233
[ Man ]
Viewer beware.

00:24.233 --> 00:26.233
You're in for a scare.

00:28.733 --> 00:30.000
Goosebumps.

00:30.433 --> 00:32.433
[ Crow Cawing ]

00:33.433 --> 00:35.433
[ Bells Tolling ]

00:51.067 --> 00:53.533
[ Chair Creaking ]

00:57.033 --> 00:58.933
[ Voice Laughing ]

01:10.100 --> 01:12.100
Karlsville is open.

01:12.600 --> 01:14.600
Time to play.

01:17.600 --> 01:19.600
[ Laughing ]

01:22.767 --> 01:24.767
[ Continues Laughing ]

01:36.267 --> 01:39.267
Good morning, guys and girls,
this is G.B. Radio 320.

01:39.267 --> 01:42.233
It's gonna be a hot one today.
It's gonna climb way up there.

01:42.233 --> 01:45.167
[ Music Playing ]

01:47.200 --> 01:49.833
[ People Chattering ]

01:49.833 --> 01:53.567
# Show me the money,
I'll show you the good time #

01:53.567 --> 01:55.367
Todd, what a pig!

01:55.367 --> 01:57.433
You're damaging the merchandise.

01:57.433 --> 01:59.567
This is a Cal Ripken rookie card.

02:00.000 --> 02:01.000
It's worth a fortune.

02:01.000 --> 02:03.867
What's the big deal?
Who's gonna notice?

02:06.000 --> 02:08.567
Jessica Walters, quick.

02:12.867 --> 02:15.067
Uh, hey, Jessica.

02:15.067 --> 02:16.500
Hey, Matthew.

02:17.167 --> 02:19.067
- Selling any good cards today?
- Uh, no.

02:19.067 --> 02:21.633
- We already sold all the cards.
- Yeah.

02:22.067 --> 02:24.900
Sold them all, huh?
That is too bad.

02:24.900 --> 02:29.267
But, you know, Matthew, I am in the
market for some new furniture, and...

02:29.767 --> 02:31.333
[ Woman ]
What about that one?

02:31.333 --> 02:33.333
This would go great in my room.

02:33.833 --> 02:34.767
[ Sighs ]

02:35.233 --> 02:37.800
- How much for the desk?
- The desk isn't for sale.

02:38.233 --> 02:39.733
[ Woman ]
Good morning, Jessica.

02:39.733 --> 02:41.733
[ Jessica ]
Good morning, Mrs. Erikson.

02:41.733 --> 02:44.967
So, you're sure you don't want to
sell this desk?

02:44.967 --> 02:46.833
Of course,
we're selling the desk.

02:46.833 --> 02:47.833
- [ Sighs ]
- Oh.

02:47.833 --> 02:50.767
- [ Mathew's Mom ] Make an offer.
- Let's see, um...

02:52.167 --> 02:56.433
- How about $20.
- OK, fine, you win.

02:56.433 --> 03:00.300
- But no deals.
- These cards are in mint condition.

03:03.167 --> 03:07.100
- [ Sighs ]
- [ Woman ] That's great.

03:07.600 --> 03:09.100
[ Man ]
How much are these books?

03:09.100 --> 03:13.033
[ Sniffing ] Mmm.
Strawberry. My favorite flavor.

03:14.833 --> 03:16.667
I'll give you $2 for it.

03:17.100 --> 03:22.000
$2?
This card is in mint condition.

03:22.000 --> 03:25.967
- This card is a collectible.
- $2. Not a penny more.

03:25.967 --> 03:27.967
But you only paid
Bobby Stanley a buck for it.

03:27.967 --> 03:29.600
Todd!

03:30.100 --> 03:31.667
# Money #

03:32.100 --> 03:34.567
Fine. $2.

03:35.000 --> 03:39.167
- Uh, do you have change for a 20?
- No.

03:39.167 --> 03:41.433
Oh, well.
[ Laughs ]

03:41.433 --> 03:44.367
The only other bill I have is...

03:44.767 --> 03:46.933
[ Sighing ]
Well, it's just a 1.

03:48.833 --> 03:50.833
[ Matthew ]
Fine just take it and get out of here.

03:50.833 --> 03:53.133
# I need money #

03:54.067 --> 03:57.067
- [ Computer Beeps ]
- # I want money #

03:57.067 --> 03:58.067
# Money #

03:59.067 --> 04:00.900
# M-O-N-E-Y #

04:01.333 --> 04:02.800
# Money #

04:02.800 --> 04:05.167
# Somebody give me some cash #

04:05.167 --> 04:06.767
# Money #

04:06.767 --> 04:09.700
# I need lots of money #

04:09.700 --> 04:11.200
# Money #

04:11.700 --> 04:13.933
[ Knocking On Door ]

04:13.933 --> 04:18.333
Uh, hey, Jess.
Um, could I talk to you for a minute?

04:18.333 --> 04:19.933
Yeah, sure.

04:19.933 --> 04:23.867
Well, um... Well, Mom and Dad's
anniversary is next week

04:23.867 --> 04:26.133
and I found them a--
a great picture frame,

04:26.133 --> 04:28.067
sterling silver.

04:28.067 --> 04:30.467
Oh, Mom loves pictures.
Yeah, it's the perfect gift.

04:30.467 --> 04:34.733
Oh, yeah, yeah.
It would be, if I could afford it.

04:35.167 --> 04:37.767
Look, I... I just need to borrow
some money, I'll pay you back.

04:37.767 --> 04:40.833
[ Sighs ]
Sam, with what?

04:41.267 --> 04:42.933
I have told you a million times.

04:43.367 --> 04:46.333
Yeah, I know, I know.
I've got to start saving my money.

04:46.833 --> 04:50.700
You waste it on games,
and candy, and toys. For what?

04:50.700 --> 04:52.933
Well, how about for fun?

04:53.433 --> 04:55.433
[ Sam ]
Look, Jess, I don't want to

04:55.433 --> 04:57.933
sit around all day
counting money like you do.

04:57.933 --> 04:59.367
So I guess that's a no.

04:59.367 --> 05:01.267
- Of course not.
- Hmm?

05:01.267 --> 05:04.600
I never give up a good business
opportunity when I see one.

05:04.600 --> 05:07.067
Let's see,
today's prime rate closed at 6%,

05:07.067 --> 05:13.200
so, I will loan you the money
at 3 points overtime, that is 9%.

05:13.200 --> 05:15.967
[ Sighs ] Forget it.
I'll make 'em a key chain.

05:19.733 --> 05:24.800
Jessica, before you sit back to
contemplate your financial empire,

05:24.800 --> 05:26.867
I need you
to sweep out the attic.

05:26.867 --> 05:28.833
[ Sighing ] Mom, I don't want to
spend my whole afternoon

05:28.833 --> 05:30.267
in some creepy old attic.

05:30.267 --> 05:32.900
But if you don't do it,
Sam gets your allowance for the week.

05:32.900 --> 05:34.900
Well, that's not fair.

05:39.900 --> 05:41.400
[ Grunts ]

05:42.900 --> 05:44.900
Yuck.

05:53.400 --> 05:55.400
[ Sighs ]

06:08.767 --> 06:10.017
Cool.

06:12.233 --> 06:14.733
What a cute little town.

06:19.733 --> 06:22.200
"Karlsville the Collector's Edition."

06:22.200 --> 06:24.133
This could be worth a fortune.

06:30.233 --> 06:33.167
Hello, Mom, it's Jessica.
Can you come up here?

06:33.167 --> 06:35.033
[ Chuckling ]

06:35.033 --> 06:38.033
Are you OK? What is it?

06:38.033 --> 06:40.533
Over here.
I want to show you something.

06:42.033 --> 06:44.600
It's some kind of miniature town.

06:44.600 --> 06:47.333
Wow.
This is really something.

06:47.333 --> 06:51.033
- I wonder who left it here.
- Probably the previous owners.

06:51.033 --> 06:53.900
- Could I have it?
- Sure. Looks like fun.

06:54.833 --> 06:56.233
Fun.

06:56.233 --> 06:58.667
It's a collector's edition.
Could be worth something.

06:58.667 --> 07:00.600
I'll sell it
and make some money.

07:00.600 --> 07:03.033
You can keep the model town.
But don't sell it.

07:03.533 --> 07:05.533
I want you to share it
with your brother.

07:05.533 --> 07:08.733
[ Sighs ]
She has no business sense.

07:09.167 --> 07:11.167
[ Cell Phone Rings ]

07:11.167 --> 07:12.667
Jessica Walters speaking.

07:12.667 --> 07:14.667
[ Cell Phone Rings ]

07:16.167 --> 07:17.800
[ Phone Ringing ]

07:23.767 --> 07:25.733
That's weird.

07:26.733 --> 07:28.900
[ Phone Continues Ringing ]

07:39.233 --> 07:41.167
[ Gasps ]

07:41.667 --> 07:43.833
[ Phone Continues Ringing ]

07:43.833 --> 07:46.467
Where am I?
What is this place?

07:47.467 --> 07:48.217
Oh.

07:55.700 --> 07:58.200
Hello? Who is this?

07:58.200 --> 08:01.700
Karl.
But my friends call me Karl.

08:01.700 --> 08:04.200
What's happening?
Where am I?

08:04.200 --> 08:07.700
Karlsville. It's a small town
with big opportunities.

08:07.700 --> 08:11.200
You like a good business opportunity,
don't you, Jessica?

08:11.200 --> 08:13.200
How did you know my name?

08:13.200 --> 08:16.200
Names aren't important,
opportunities are.

08:16.200 --> 08:21.200
And an opportunity awaits you.
Step outside and look for it.

08:21.200 --> 08:23.200
[ Dial Tone Buzzing ]

09:00.233 --> 09:01.833
[ Gasping ]
Oh.

09:02.267 --> 09:05.567
You're right on time.
I've been waiting. We spoke earlier?

09:06.000 --> 09:08.700
- Earlier?
- On the phone.

09:09.133 --> 09:10.633
Karl.

09:10.633 --> 09:12.733
I know who you are. I--
I just don't know who you are.

09:13.233 --> 09:17.133
Ah. I'm a businessman.
I own this place.

09:17.133 --> 09:18.633
What place?

09:18.633 --> 09:23.133
Karlsville. It's my town.
And I'm looking for a partner.

09:23.133 --> 09:26.133
Someone who understands
a good business opportunity.

09:26.133 --> 09:28.633
Someone who likes
to make money.

09:28.633 --> 09:30.967
I thought that someone
might be you.

09:30.967 --> 09:32.967
Look, I don't even know
how I got here.

09:32.967 --> 09:36.067
Oh, who knows how they end up
where they do.

09:36.067 --> 09:37.667
Is that a no?

09:39.100 --> 09:41.700
- What kind of opportunity?
- The beverage business.

09:41.700 --> 09:43.700
- Beverage?
- You're gonna love it.

09:43.700 --> 09:46.200
Selling lemonade.

09:46.900 --> 09:48.833
[ Scoffing ]
Lemonade.

09:49.333 --> 09:51.800
I'm looking for serious
business opportunities here.

09:51.800 --> 09:55.400
- I'm not selling lemonade.
- Karlsville has many opportunities.

09:55.400 --> 09:58.667
We'll start small, see how you do,
and grow from there.

10:00.067 --> 10:01.567
Besides,

10:02.500 --> 10:04.900
this isn't just any lemonade.

10:04.900 --> 10:08.367
# You got it made in the shade
with Karl's lemonade, yeah #

10:09.067 --> 10:12.100
It's my own special blend.

10:12.100 --> 10:14.600
People can't resist it.

10:22.333 --> 10:24.267
[ Sniffing ]

10:24.767 --> 10:27.567
You'll make a fortune.

10:28.433 --> 10:31.033
- Deal?
- I get 50%?

10:31.033 --> 10:34.067
Ouch.
You drive a hard bargain.

10:34.767 --> 10:37.700
- Deal.
- Deal. Great.

10:38.200 --> 10:41.567
I want you to meet our employee,
Nikki.

10:41.567 --> 10:45.700
Nikki, I want you to meet my new
business partner Jessica, Jessica...

10:45.700 --> 10:47.133
- Walters.
- Whatever.

10:47.133 --> 10:49.200
She's in charge.
She knows business.

10:49.200 --> 10:51.600
Knows what to do.
Knows how to make a buck.

10:51.600 --> 10:56.233
You listen to her,
do whatever she says.

10:56.233 --> 10:59.233
Let's see if we have
everything we need.

11:01.233 --> 11:01.953
Ah-ha.

11:04.700 --> 11:07.233
Now, Nikki,

11:08.667 --> 11:10.667
don't raise prices.

11:10.667 --> 11:12.167
I wouldn't wanna be accused

11:12.167 --> 11:14.667
of unfair business practices
in my own town.

11:14.667 --> 11:19.167
And, I can't be responsible
for what happens to

11:20.100 --> 11:22.000
greedy little pigs.

11:23.667 --> 11:25.633
Good luck.

11:27.867 --> 11:29.367
Hmm.

11:30.367 --> 11:33.367
Time to turn up the heat.

11:41.833 --> 11:43.167
[ Laughing ]

11:45.667 --> 11:48.700
Well, let's see
how good this stuff really is.

11:50.067 --> 11:53.400
- Watch, listen, and learn.
- [ Baby Whimpering ]

11:53.400 --> 11:55.900
- Good afternoon.
- Oh, hello, there.

11:55.900 --> 11:57.900
[ Laughing ]
Oh, what a lovely baby.

11:58.400 --> 11:59.900
[ Laughing ]
Thank you.

11:59.900 --> 12:00.900
Lemonade?

12:01.400 --> 12:02.900
All right. All right.

12:03.400 --> 12:04.400
It is warming up a bit,
isn't it?

12:04.900 --> 12:06.400
Yes, this will cool you
right down.

12:12.167 --> 12:13.933
Well, thank you.

12:18.267 --> 12:22.000
Ah. Well, that is the best lemonade
I've ever had.

12:22.000 --> 12:24.100
- How much do I owe you?
- $1.

12:24.100 --> 12:26.100
Oh, that's all?

12:26.100 --> 12:28.133
Well, give me 2 more then.

12:37.367 --> 12:39.800
Hmm. Well, thank you.
Good day.

12:41.800 --> 12:43.800
[ Sighing ]
Good day, girls.

12:43.800 --> 12:46.800
A little something
to wet the whistle if I might.

12:46.800 --> 12:50.567
Boy, it's a hot one today,
don't fill it up. Just half way.

12:52.500 --> 12:54.767
Here you are, sir.

12:56.767 --> 13:00.400
- Refreshing. How much?
- $1.

13:00.400 --> 13:03.200
That would be a bargain
at twice the price.

13:03.633 --> 13:04.500
[ Echoing ]
Twice the price.

13:04.500 --> 13:06.467
Twice the price.

13:08.400 --> 13:10.400
Good day, Killman.

13:10.400 --> 13:13.567
It's a scorcher, isn't it?
Give me a lemonade.

13:14.533 --> 13:15.833
What's the damage?

13:15.833 --> 13:17.600
- $1--
- $2.

13:18.033 --> 13:18.783
$2.

13:24.367 --> 13:26.767
$2 doesn't seem like enough

13:27.267 --> 13:29.800
for such
a delightful lemon beverage.

13:30.300 --> 13:33.000
You could charge a fortune.

13:33.000 --> 13:34.867
[ Echoing ]
Fortune. Fortune.

13:34.867 --> 13:36.400
Thank you.

13:36.400 --> 13:39.767
I don't think that was such a good idea.
You heard what Karl said.

13:39.767 --> 13:41.700
And you heard the customers.

13:41.700 --> 13:43.867
It's called supply and demand.

13:44.367 --> 13:47.367
They like the supply
and we demand more money.

13:48.867 --> 13:51.667
[ Sighs ]
You pour, I'll price.

13:54.733 --> 13:57.633
- Now what are you doing?
- Increasing our inventory.

13:58.067 --> 14:00.633
- That's cheating.
- It's not cheating.

14:01.633 --> 14:03.400
It's business.

14:07.033 --> 14:08.467
# Oh, money #

14:08.467 --> 14:09.467
# Money, money, money #

14:09.467 --> 14:11.767
# Show me the money, baby #

14:12.167 --> 14:14.033
# Show me the money #

14:14.033 --> 14:17.867
- Thank you.
- [ People Clamoring ]

14:17.867 --> 14:19.300
# Show me the money #

14:19.300 --> 14:23.633
# I'll show you a good time, yeah #

14:24.067 --> 14:27.167
# I'm not talking 'about
the place or the name #

14:27.167 --> 14:29.233
# Giving the money
to the woman with the rhythm #

14:30.967 --> 14:34.400
[ People Clamoring ]

14:36.200 --> 14:38.467
# Ooh, money #

14:39.133 --> 14:40.933
Hey, quit pushing.

14:41.933 --> 14:43.467
Pour, Nikki, pour.

14:43.467 --> 14:46.267
Look at these people,
what happened to them?

14:46.267 --> 14:49.100
Who cares?
Look at all this cash.

14:53.100 --> 14:54.467
[ People Shouting ]

14:54.467 --> 14:57.467
[ Woman ] Excuse me.
Coming through. Hey, come on.

14:57.467 --> 14:59.367
# Show me the money, baby #

14:59.367 --> 15:01.367
# Show me the money #

15:01.367 --> 15:03.400
# Money, money, money, money #

15:03.900 --> 15:05.233
# Money #

15:05.233 --> 15:07.133
# Show me the money, money #

15:07.133 --> 15:08.900
# I'll show you a good time #

15:08.900 --> 15:10.400
Excuse me.
Excuse me, everybody.

15:10.833 --> 15:12.833
I have an announcement to make.

15:12.833 --> 15:15.533
- We're all out of lemonade.
- [ All Gasping ]

15:15.533 --> 15:17.467
There's only one glass left.

15:17.900 --> 15:20.400
Out of lemonade?
How can that be?

15:21.333 --> 15:23.333
- We want more!
- [ All Clamoring ]

15:23.767 --> 15:26.100
OK, calm down, everyone,
calm down!

15:26.100 --> 15:28.167
There is one glass left.

15:28.167 --> 15:31.300
And I will be happy
to sell it to the highest bidder.

15:32.467 --> 15:34.633
- What're you doing?
- Just listen.

15:35.067 --> 15:36.867
- I'll give you $10.
- [ Woman ] Make that $20.

15:36.867 --> 15:38.867
- [ Woman #2 ] $25!
- [ Man # 1 ] 30!

15:40.700 --> 15:43.267
- $50!
- $100!

15:43.933 --> 15:46.300
[ People Exclaiming ]

15:46.733 --> 15:48.100
[ Baby Whimpering ]

15:54.000 --> 15:58.200
She had more all along.
She was squeezing us.

15:58.200 --> 16:00.633
- Yeah.
- Please, please...

16:00.633 --> 16:03.600
She's nothing
but a greedy little pig.

16:03.600 --> 16:05.067
[ Echoing ]
Pig. Pig.

16:06.000 --> 16:07.833
[ People Murmuring ]

16:08.733 --> 16:11.767
Karl told you not to be greedy,
but you didn't listen.

16:12.433 --> 16:15.033
You're nothing
but a greedy little pig.

16:16.100 --> 16:18.067
- Get the pig.
- No.

16:18.067 --> 16:22.233
Pig goes great with lemonade.

16:22.667 --> 16:27.000
[ Groaning ]
But it's not my fault. Karl set me up.

16:27.000 --> 16:29.267
- Karl?
- The man who owns the town.

16:29.267 --> 16:32.800
- Karl could help?
- Of course, he could.

16:32.800 --> 16:36.933
Karl loves bacon.
Karl!

16:37.633 --> 16:39.633
[ Karl Laughing ]

16:40.433 --> 16:43.467
- Get the pig.
- No!

16:43.467 --> 16:45.700
[ People Clamoring ]

16:47.167 --> 16:49.200
[ Laughing ]

16:58.633 --> 17:00.633
What's happening to me?

17:01.700 --> 17:02.200
[ Groaning ]

17:02.933 --> 17:05.267
I guess our little partnership
must be dissolved.

17:05.267 --> 17:07.599
What have you done to me?
[ Sobbing ]

17:07.599 --> 17:09.367
You hogged the profits.

17:09.367 --> 17:13.133
I should have known you were
nothing but a greedy little pig.

17:13.633 --> 17:14.733
[ Screams ]

17:14.733 --> 17:16.733
[ Sobbing ]

17:16.733 --> 17:18.599
[ Karl Laughing ]

17:28.200 --> 17:30.133
[ Grunts ]

17:30.133 --> 17:32.967
You don't belong in business.
You don't have the head for it.

17:32.967 --> 17:34.467
[ Laughing ]

17:35.267 --> 17:37.100
- There she is!
- [ Gasps ]

17:37.600 --> 17:39.100
[ All Clamoring ]

17:47.667 --> 17:49.167
[ Sobbing ]

17:52.900 --> 17:54.433
Here's your money!

17:54.433 --> 17:56.333
[ All Screaming ]

17:59.467 --> 18:00.800
[ Panting ]

18:01.300 --> 18:03.433
911.

18:05.500 --> 18:09.100
[ Male Operator ] 911.
This number is no longer in service.

18:09.100 --> 18:10.600
Oh!

18:11.667 --> 18:13.667
Call home. That's it.

18:13.667 --> 18:15.567
[ People Clamoring ]

18:18.200 --> 18:20.567
- [ Busy Signal Beeping ]
- No!

18:20.567 --> 18:22.533
[ Women Screaming ]

18:22.533 --> 18:23.967
Cell phone!

18:24.367 --> 18:27.300
- Get the pig!
- No. Oh, no!

18:27.800 --> 18:29.433
[ All Clamoring ]

18:31.367 --> 18:34.367
- [ Cell Phone Ringing ]
- [ People Clamoring ]

18:35.367 --> 18:37.067
[ Ringing ]

18:37.533 --> 18:38.833
[ Screams ]

18:39.533 --> 18:42.800
[ All ] Get the pig!
Get the pig!

18:43.767 --> 18:45.567
Get the pig! Get the pig!

18:45.567 --> 18:47.733
Somebody pick up the phone!

18:47.733 --> 18:51.233
- [ Cell Phone Continues Ringing ]
- [ People Clamoring ]

18:59.800 --> 19:02.267
- [ Ringing ]
- Jessica.

19:02.267 --> 19:04.833
[ All ]
Get the pig! Come on!

19:04.833 --> 19:06.433
Jessica?

19:06.867 --> 19:08.733
[ All Clamoring ]

19:12.300 --> 19:14.367
[ Cell Phone Continues Ringing ]

19:14.367 --> 19:17.200
- Hello?
- [ Screams ]

19:17.200 --> 19:19.700
- [ Sam Gasps ]
- [ Grunts ]

19:23.633 --> 19:25.300
[ Sighs ]

19:25.733 --> 19:27.733
Oh, thank you, Sam.

19:27.733 --> 19:29.333
Thank you for taking my call.

19:29.833 --> 19:33.333
- What happened?
- You don't want to know.

19:34.833 --> 19:37.533
Sam, grab the other end.

19:39.533 --> 19:42.367
W-well, you just
can't throw it away.

